Hyperparameters related to EWC

loss: mse # When calculating the Fisher information, the loss criterion for gradient calculation.

continue:
  use_statistic_values_of_checkpoint: True # I recommend setting this to True.
  checkpoint: '/data/tmp/univ_checkpoints/checkpoint_1275.pth' # The potential used in the calculation of EWC
  calc_fisher: False # Whether to precompute Fisher information
  opt_params: 'opt_params_sevenn.pkl' # Precomputed optimized parameters file of the Pretrained model
  fisher_information: 'fisher_sevenn.pkl' # Precomputed Fisher information file of the Pretrained model
  ewc_lambda: 5.0 # The lambda term of the EWC loss

load_dataset_path: # When calculating the Fisher information, this data will be used for precomputation.


In step 1, Fisher information and optimized parameters are calculated for the training set using the checkpoint potential file. The outputs are fisher_sevenn.pkl and opt_params_sevenn.pkl.
In step 2, training starts by applying EWC from the checkpoint. The loss written in the log.* is the loss without EWC summation. An update is planned for the future. (For those interested in the EWC loss, it is currently necessary to manually log and track it.)